1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,576
Welcome to Cultivating Self Qualities.

2
00:00:03,576 --> 00:00:10,157
In this practice, we will gently explore
the eight C’s of Self: curiosity,

3
00:00:10,157 --> 00:00:16,107
calmness, compassion, confidence,
courage, creativity, clarity, and

4
00:00:16,107 --> 00:00:17,369
connectedness.

5
00:00:17,369 --> 00:00:19,505
You do not need to feel all of them.

6
00:00:19,505 --> 00:00:25,728
You are simply noticing what is available
and what may be asking for support.

7
00:00:25,728 --> 00:00:28,886
Begin by settling your body.

8
00:00:28,886 --> 00:00:31,719
Let yourself arrive.

9
00:00:31,719 --> 00:00:34,087
Take a slow breath in.

10
00:00:43,087 --> 00:00:43,087
<break time="3s" />

11
00:00:43,087 --> 00:00:44,480
And let it out.

12
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,034
Now notice what is present inside.

13
00:00:47,034 --> 00:00:48,102
Maybe thoughts.

14
00:00:48,102 --> 00:00:49,588
Maybe sensations.

15
00:00:49,588 --> 00:00:50,842
Maybe emotions.

16
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:52,607
Maybe parts.

17
00:00:52,607 --> 00:00:56,090
Let everything be here without needing to
change it.

18
00:00:56,090 --> 00:00:58,551
We will begin with curiosity.

19
00:00:58,551 --> 00:01:04,833
If imagery feels supportive, you might
imagine curiosity as a warm golden light

20
00:01:04,833 --> 00:01:10,632
in the mind's eye — not bright or
forceful, just gently illuminating what

21
00:01:10,632 --> 00:01:11,276
is here.

22
00:01:23,276 --> 00:01:23,276
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

23
00:01:23,276 --> 00:01:28,873
Curiosity is the quality of turning
toward your inner world with interest

24
00:01:28,873 --> 00:01:30,428
instead of judgment.

25
00:01:48,428 --> 00:01:48,428
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

26
00:01:48,428 --> 00:01:49,589
Ask inside:

27
00:02:01,589 --> 00:02:01,589
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

28
00:02:01,589 --> 00:02:03,957
What am I noticing right now?

29
00:02:15,957 --> 00:02:15,957
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

30
00:02:15,957 --> 00:02:16,839
Now ask:

31
00:02:28,839 --> 00:02:28,839
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

32
00:02:28,839 --> 00:02:31,765
Can I be just a little curious about
this?

33
00:02:43,765 --> 00:02:43,765
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

34
00:02:43,765 --> 00:02:48,316
If curiosity is not available, notice the
part that blocks it.

35
00:02:48,316 --> 00:02:50,545
That part may have a good reason.

36
00:02:50,545 --> 00:02:51,845
Now calmness.

37
00:02:51,845 --> 00:02:55,049
Calmness does not mean everything is
peaceful.

38
00:02:55,049 --> 00:03:00,297
It may simply mean there is a little more
space around what is happening.

39
00:03:00,297 --> 00:03:01,412
Notice your breath.

40
00:03:01,412 --> 00:03:04,431
Notice the support underneath you.

41
00:03:04,431 --> 00:03:06,149
Ask:

42
00:03:06,149 --> 00:03:11,490
Is there any place inside or around me
that feels even slightly calmer?

43
00:03:23,490 --> 00:03:23,490
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

44
00:03:23,490 --> 00:03:25,162
Now compassion.

45
00:03:25,162 --> 00:03:30,419
If imagery feels supportive, you might
imagine compassion as a soft warmth

46
00:03:30,419 --> 00:03:35,100
around the heart — like sitting near a
quiet hearth on a cold day.

47
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:47,100
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

48
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:52,533
Compassion is the ability to be with pain
without turning against it.

49
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:53,880
Ask:

50
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:58,106
Is there a part of me that could use
kindness right now?

51
00:04:10,106 --> 00:04:10,106
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

52
00:04:10,106 --> 00:04:13,171
If compassion feels difficult, ask:

53
00:04:13,171 --> 00:04:16,886
What part of me is afraid of compassion?

54
00:04:28,886 --> 00:04:28,886
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

55
00:04:28,886 --> 00:04:31,254
Now confidence.

56
00:04:31,254 --> 00:04:35,387
Confidence in IFS does not mean forcing
certainty.

57
00:04:35,387 --> 00:04:40,495
It means sensing that you can be present
with your parts, even slowly.

58
00:04:40,495 --> 00:04:41,981
Ask:

59
00:04:41,981 --> 00:04:45,510
What helps me trust myself, even a
little?

60
00:04:57,510 --> 00:04:57,510
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

61
00:04:57,510 --> 00:04:59,135
Now courage.

62
00:04:59,135 --> 00:05:03,129
Courage may be the willingness to notice
something honestly.

63
00:05:03,129 --> 00:05:04,708
Ask:

64
00:05:04,708 --> 00:05:09,027
What feels brave about being here with
myself right now?

65
00:05:21,027 --> 00:05:21,027
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

66
00:05:21,027 --> 00:05:22,652
Now creativity.

67
00:05:22,652 --> 00:05:27,389
Creativity is the possibility that there
may be new choices.

68
00:05:27,389 --> 00:05:28,643
Ask:

69
00:05:28,643 --> 00:05:33,473
What new option might my system not have
considered yet?

70
00:05:45,473 --> 00:05:45,473
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

71
00:05:45,473 --> 00:05:46,634
Now clarity.

72
00:05:46,634 --> 00:05:52,528
Clarity is seeing what is happening
without becoming completely blended with

73
00:05:52,528 --> 00:05:52,764
it.

74
00:05:52,764 --> 00:05:53,925
Ask:

75
00:05:53,925 --> 00:05:58,197
What do I understand a little more
clearly right now?

76
00:06:10,197 --> 00:06:10,197
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

77
00:06:10,197 --> 00:06:11,730
Now connectedness.

78
00:06:11,730 --> 00:06:17,434
If imagery feels supportive, you might
imagine all the qualities gathering as a

79
00:06:17,434 --> 00:06:23,212
soft white-gold light in the heart — not
to erase your parts, but to remind them

80
00:06:23,212 --> 00:06:24,455
that they belong.

81
00:06:36,455 --> 00:06:36,455
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

82
00:06:36,455 --> 00:06:41,815
Connectedness may be connection to your
body, to your parts, to another person,

83
00:06:41,815 --> 00:06:44,907
to the present moment, or to something
larger.

84
00:06:44,907 --> 00:06:45,743
Ask:

85
00:06:45,743 --> 00:06:48,576
What helps me feel less alone?

86
00:07:00,576 --> 00:07:00,576
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

87
00:07:00,576 --> 00:07:05,545
Now take a moment to notice which Self
quality felt most available today.

88
00:07:05,545 --> 00:07:09,074
And which quality felt least available.

89
00:07:09,074 --> 00:07:11,396
There is no failure here.

90
00:07:11,396 --> 00:07:17,062
The less available quality may show you
where a protective part needs attention.

91
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:23,063
Now imagine placing the most available
quality near a part of you that needs

92
00:07:23,063 --> 00:07:23,703
support.

93
00:07:35,703 --> 00:07:35,703
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

94
00:07:35,703 --> 00:07:39,975
If calmness was available, let calmness
be near that part.

95
00:07:39,975 --> 00:07:46,384
If curiosity was available, let curiosity
gently turn toward that part.

96
00:07:46,384 --> 00:07:51,585
If compassion was available, let
compassion soften around that part.

97
00:07:51,585 --> 00:07:53,396
Silently say:

98
00:08:02,396 --> 00:08:02,396
<break time="3s" />

99
00:08:02,396 --> 00:08:04,439
I do not need to become perfect.

100
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:07,179
I can practice returning to Self-energy.

101
00:08:07,179 --> 00:08:10,198
One quality at a time is enough.

102
00:08:10,198 --> 00:08:12,241
Take a slow breath in.

103
00:08:21,241 --> 00:08:21,241
<break time="3s" />

104
00:08:21,241 --> 00:08:23,470
And let it out.

105
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:27,232
When you are ready, return your attention
to the room.

106
00:08:27,232 --> 00:08:31,365
Notice one Self quality you want to carry
with you today.

107
00:08:31,365 --> 00:08:36,969
Let that quality be like a small lantern
you do not have to hold perfectly. It can

108
00:08:36,969 --> 00:08:41,535
flicker. It can be faint. It can still
help you find your way back.

109
00:08:50,535 --> 00:08:50,535
<break time="3s" />

